cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL 

This paper deals with unsupervised visual descriptors compression, which is a key ingredient of large-scale image retrieval systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses similarity search, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The proposed architecture is based on deep learning, which is a common topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also evaluates its approach on several datasets, which is a common practice in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of its approach on visual descriptors, which is a common topic in cs.CL (Computation and Language).
